Wash and dry produce.

Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch pieces and place in a #medium pot{}
with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until
tender, ~{10-12%minutes}. Reserve 1⁄2 cup potato cooking liquid
(3⁄4 cup for 4 servings), then drain.

Return potatoes to #pot{} and mash with half the @sour cream{3%tablespoon}
and 1 TBSP @butter{} (2 TBSP for 4) until smooth and creamy, adding splashes of
reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Taste and season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While potatoes cook, trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites
from greens. Trim, peel, and quarter @carrots{6%ounce} lengthwise; thinly slice
crosswise into quarter-moons.

Open package of @ground beef{10%ounce} and drain off any excess liquid.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add
chicken, scallion whites, carrots, and half the @dried thyme{1%teaspoon}
(all for 4 servings); season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally,
until chicken is browned and nearly cooked through, ~{4-5%minutes} (chicken
will finish cooking in the next step).

> Swap in beef or turkey for chicken. Cook as instructed, breaking up meat
> into pieces.

Stir in @garlic powder{1%teaspoon} and 1 TBSP @butter{} (2 TBSP for 4). Cook,
stirring constantly, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Sprinkle @flour{1%tablespoon} evenly over chicken mixture; stir to combine.

Add 1 cup water (2 cups for 4 servings), @peas{4%ounce}, @chicken stock concentrate{2%unit}, and remaining sour cream; cook, whisking constantly, until
gravy has thickened and chicken is cooked through, ~{3-4%minutes} (if gravy
seems too thick, add more water 1 TBSP at a time). Taste and season with
salt and pepper if desired.

Divide sour cream mashed potatoes between shallow #bowls{}. Top with crustless
chicken pot pie and garnish with scallion greens. Serve.

> Ground Meat is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.